1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:31,200
The speaker quotes Scripture, tells stories, and uses proper punctuation, capitalization, and complete sentences.

2
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,640
And so today I want to look at marriage.

3
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:39,360
And for those of you not married at this time, I hope this will be an encouragement to you.

4
00:00:40,730 --> 00:00:44,870
I want to begin by starting off with something that might sound familiar to you.

5
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:50,060
He knows I don't like to talk in the morning.

6
00:00:52,550 --> 00:00:54,670
Why can't she just trust me?

7
00:00:54,670 --> 00:00:57,370
We've done fine so far, haven't we?

8
00:00:59,290 --> 00:01:00,910
Doesn't he know I'm busy?

9
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,060
Can't she see that I'm tired?

10
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:09,780
I'll spend my money the way I want to.

11
00:01:11,850 --> 00:01:12,970
I have feelings too.

12
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:15,670
Doesn't anybody understand that?

13
00:01:15,830 --> 00:01:17,210
I'm a person too.

14
00:01:19,230 --> 00:01:20,750
I wish he wouldn't act that way.

15
00:01:22,220 --> 00:01:23,940
Who does she think she is anyway?

16
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:27,340
I know he really doesn't care.

17
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:28,480
He can't.

18
00:01:29,190 --> 00:01:29,850
I know it.

19
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:32,970
Is that all the thanks I get?

20
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:36,130
Won't he ever learn?

21
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:40,380
I've just got to get out of here.

22
00:01:40,820 --> 00:01:44,500
Maybe you've had some of those feelings.

23
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:47,080
Maybe you know somebody who does.

24
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:51,800
Are there answers to the crying needs in that monologue?

25
00:01:53,110 --> 00:01:55,890
Yes. Yes, there are.

26
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,360
What does a Christian marriage look like anyway?

27
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:05,040
Outside of the walls of this church, there are lots of marriages.

28
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,820
But what does a Christian marriage look like?

29
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:13,000
You see, there can be a marriage between two people who are Christians,

30
00:02:13,380 --> 00:02:15,920
and then there's a Christian marriage.

31
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,780
and they are different.

32
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,380
And this morning I want to explore

33
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:22,520
what God says about a Christian marriage.

34
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:25,500
The Bible says,

35
00:02:25,660 --> 00:02:26,960
for this reason a man

36
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,400
will leave his father and mother

37
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,920
and be united to his wife

38
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,040
and they will become one flesh.

39
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:37,290
Friends, God can make that happen.

40
00:02:37,530 --> 00:02:39,690
A marriage relationship wrapped in unity,

41
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,490
mutual trust and respect,

42
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,230
common goals and dreams.

43
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:44,910
But sadly,

44
00:02:44,910 --> 00:02:48,870
so many marriages are not about unity

45
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:52,070
or mutual respect or common goals

46
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:55,030
instead they are either abusive

47
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:59,440
oppressive or just two individuals

48
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:02,450
two roommates going in their

49
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:05,960
separate directions but God has a

50
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:09,370
different plan for marriage and so I'm indebted

51
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:12,610
to a discipleship article years ago by Lauren White

52
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:15,310
for an outline for this message and I want to share with

53
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:19,430
you some insights from this author and from my own study of the scriptures.

54
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:23,460
Friends, if you're going to have a Christian marriage,

55
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:27,980
not just two people who are Christians, you want to make sure

56
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:31,900
that you are living out five commitments that I'm going to share

57
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:35,140
this morning. Five basic commitments.

58
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:40,570
Though many marriages break up over the big three, and I share this with

59
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:44,690
couples as they sit before marriage counseling with me, here are the big three.

60
00:03:44,690 --> 00:03:53,000
money sex and communication if things go awry there marriages often can dissolve but i think

61
00:03:53,000 --> 00:04:01,450
those are symptoms of even deeper issues and these five commitments i think help us to combat

62
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:10,920
the symptoms of breakdown and so here's the first one number one a commitment to grow in christ

63
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:13,460
for the rest of your life.

64
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,730
If you are going to have a Christian marriage,

65
00:04:18,030 --> 00:04:20,690
you must be committed to grow in Christ

66
00:04:20,690 --> 00:04:22,050
each and every day.

67
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:23,750
You never get to plateau.

68
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:27,610
You never get to stop growing.

69
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,440
The Christian life is a life of learning

70
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,780
and growing and maturing.

71
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:34,580
We can always learn more.

72
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,900
We can always stretch a little more.

73
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:39,240
Friends, we're only going to be perfect

74
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:43,240
when we finally see Jesus face to face.

75
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:48,730
And until then, it's a growing, maturing process.

76
00:04:50,390 --> 00:05:00,950
And if we don't grow with Christ, then our relationships around us begin to stagnate as well, including marriages.

77
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:04,240
Ephesians chapter 4, Paul writes,

78
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:11,320
We will hold to the truth in love, becoming, listen, more and more in every way like Christ,

79
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,020
who is the head of His body, the church.

80
00:05:15,110 --> 00:05:16,750
More and more.

81
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:25,110
Here's Paul. To me, I think he's a mature Christian, writing, we're going to grow more and more each and every day.

82
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:31,130
Marriage is an ever-changing, dynamic relationship through the ups and the downs of life.

83
00:05:31,870 --> 00:05:39,930
To keep that relationship vibrant, we must continually be growing in wisdom, character, and responsibility.

84
00:05:40,630 --> 00:05:46,980
It takes an open, teachable person to develop the characteristics to be a good, healthy marriage partner.

85
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,300
You can't have a closed mind.

86
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:52,680
You can't go before the Lord and say, I am done.

87
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,480
I like the way I am just right here.

88
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,920
Because your spouse will outgrow you.

89
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,620
How do you become like that?

90
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:03,940
You do it through Christ.

91
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,480
That's the heart of what it means to have a Christian marriage.

92
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,220
Two people without Christ can have a marriage.

93
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,380
Two Christians can have a marriage.

94
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:16,740
But without a commitment to growing in Christ for the rest of your life,

95
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:20,530
you don't really have a Christian marriage.

96
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:32,340
My question is this, will you commit to growing in Christ for the rest of your life?

97
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,660
That's a bold commitment.

98
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:40,180
But if marriages are going to survive, and not just survive, but thrive,

99
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:44,800
we need to be committed each and every day, first of all, to Jesus,

100
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:50,240
and to grow, and to be stretched all along the way.

101
00:06:50,400 --> 00:07:02,480
Number two, commitment number two is to stay committed to our marriages for life

102
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:06,020
and to work and solve the problems that arise.

103
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:11,600
Many marriages are on the rocks these days, sadly, both inside and outside the church.

104
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:17,720
And I so often see this mentality in our culture today that it's kind of like,

105
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:22,120
I'm going to have this marriage until something better comes along

106
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,820
or until things just don't work out.

107
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:32,770
This is fine for now, but we don't commit to really work it out.

108
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:38,140
Malachi chapter 2, the Bible says, God says, you cry out.

109
00:07:38,140 --> 00:07:39,760
Why has the Lord abandoned us?

110
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:42,670
God says, I'll tell you why.

111
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:48,990
Because the Lord witnessed the vows you and your wife made to each other on your wedding day when you were young.

112
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:51,450
But you have been disloyal to her.

113
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:56,290
Though she remained your faithful companion, the wife of your marriage vows.

114
00:07:56,890 --> 00:07:59,110
Didn't the Lord make you one with your wife?

115
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:01,250
In body and spirit you are his.

116
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:03,050
And what does he want?

117
00:08:03,590 --> 00:08:05,270
Godly children from your union.

118
00:08:06,290 --> 00:08:07,490
So guard yourself.

119
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:09,810
Remain loyal to the wife of your youth.

120
00:08:10,110 --> 00:08:12,730
For I hate divorce, says the Lord, the God of Israel.

121
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:14,980
God hates it.

122
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,280
Is divorce the unforgivable sin?

123
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,680
Absolutely not.

124
00:08:19,730 --> 00:08:23,450
There is grace for those who have been through that kind of trauma.

125
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:26,070
But I want us to recapture this value

126
00:08:26,070 --> 00:08:28,810
that marriage is not to be entered in too lightly.

127
00:08:29,370 --> 00:08:33,700
And it's to be committed for life as much as we can help it.

128
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,060
When a marriage ends, it plays havoc.

129
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:42,100
work on the couple and their friends and their family and the community and the church and on

130
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:50,020
and on and on. If a marriage is in trouble, the challenge of God's Word is to do all they can to

131
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:56,720
make it work, to pray, to seek wisdom, to seek counseling, to seek accountability. Do all they

132
00:08:56,720 --> 00:09:05,900
can to make it work. Charlie Shedd wrote some books on marriage, and one has a chapter in it

133
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:12,570
that I find interesting. He wrote this chapter called The 20-Year Warm-Up, and he's saying that

134
